Comments: Cultivation of a vampire: 'Candidatus Absconditicoccus praedator'. We report the first stable cultivation of an association between the ultrasmall Candidate Phyla Radiation bacterium M39-6, which we named 'Ca. Absconditicoccus praedator', and its host Halorhodospira halophila M39-5, an obligately photosynthetic and anaerobic purple sulphur bacterium; we also carry out an in-depth characterization of their biology. Both were isolated from the hypersaline alkaline Lake Hotontyn Nur (Mongolia).

Comments: We analyzed five metagenomes of prokaryote communities that inhabit the top sediments of hypersaline soda lakes in the Kulunda Steppe (South-Western Siberia, Russian Federation). Almost thousand metagenome-assembled genomes (MAGs) from mostly uncultured and novel haloalkaliphilic prokaryotes were obtained. We described the metabolic capacities of the most abundant lineages and the first extremophilic members of the Candidate Phyla Radiant (CPR).;derived from metagenome
